div.p:
To this little Treatise, I haue adioyned the WIDDOVVES GLASSE, the which I humbly intreate you, to present, in my Name, to your two most worthy Sisters, who for the long, constant, & most exemplar professiō
of that noble, and worthy state of chast Widdowhood, may seeme to clayme a iust Title therunto. But I deemed not my labour in translating it, worthy to be presented to so honourable Matrons, in a Dedicatory a part: not doubting but the same wilbe more grateful, comming through your handes, who are so neere a kin vnto them, both by Nature & Grace;
seeing Virginity, and Widdowhood, haue euer been accounted Sisters, and betroathed to the same Eternall Spouse Christ Iesus.
